				<td colspan="2"><hr /></td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I understand that Druids are the main Hibernian healing class. With this in mind it seems wise to focus Bard spec points more toward Nurture and Music than on the Regrowth line since ideal groups at high levels will likely have a Druid as the prime healer. I've seen folks post many templates for spec point allocation however it seems to me that Bards should consider putting enough points in to reach the following minimum spec training levels for these spell lines:
<br />

<br />
27 - Regrowth. Allows for the second spell in the group healing line of spells and 4th in the group regen song line. Bards get plenty of non-spec point healing spells in the regrowth line so I did not see a need to push this spec line too far. 
<br />

<br />
33 - Nurture. Allows for next to the highest level of speed & fatigue regen plus high level of power regen. To me, fatigue and power regen appear to be the defining traits of the bard class. These are likely to be the things that make Bards most popular in groups other than the ability to run your group around far more quickly.
<br />

<br />
36 - Music. Allows high level of direct damage shout plus captivate army AE Mez spell that could have great potential in RvR play. 
<br />

<br />
With these minimum levels allocated, the rest can be applied to fine tune your character to your own tastes. I'm leaning more toward Nurture for the rest of my spec points with perhaps up to 8 into Blunt training so I can swing a weapon with at least some proficiency. 
<br />

<br />
Let me hear your feedback on where you plan to allocate your spec points and why.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
