				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Using the character builder from  <a href="http://daoc.catacombs.com" target="_blank" class="postlink">http://daoc.catacombs.com</a>  and my experiences as an EQ bard..
<br />

<br />
I tentativly plan on going:
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Nuture 43</span> to Max out Run Song and Fatique song while still haveing a real good Power Regen song to help with down time.
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Regrowth 20</span> to keep some backup/emergancy heal skills and some regen via song to help reduce down time.
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Bard Music 28</span> for a good AE Mez line.
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Blades 25</span> to help keep the Melee skills up there too.
<br />

<br />
I think the main thing a bard might bring to the group and realm might end up being in the Bard Music area..so my Nuture and Music specs might change if I observe that as being more needed then being able to run fast or regen power/endurance better.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
