				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Ransard ... the issue is not so much what you want to do ... but what the game will require at higher levels, and you and I both DO NOT KNOW what this future is going to bring this game!
<br />

<br />
This is the difficult part right now, specially for a Bard. Right now, the game is leaning towards tanking and power gaming, and the only requirements are going to be tanks and clerics ... and your role and need in any group is going to be minimal ... when there are better healers and buff'ers in the game. My suggestion to Mythic, in Beta, was to take the Bards and make them masters of Defense, so that there is a need for the Class ... but so far, the only thing that they have done is work on the fighting styles and their application. All casters are getting hammered twice more than I am, and I am getting hammered twice more than any tank I play with .... and the end result is that we can NEVER level, and stay on par with the higher levels in this game, or grow as well as they can ... meaning that your idea of buffing is good right now ... until you get to the critters that require 30 people, and no one will need your buffs, and you do not tank enough ... now we are back to EQ ... who the hell needs Bards, when you got Enchanters? And no group can survive efficiently at high levels without the tankage, the cleric and the enchanter ... end of story!
<br />

<br />
Right now, Mythic is doing exactly the same thing! Eldritch level 14, me (Bard) 14, Blademaster 15, Druid 15, shorty Rogue 16 ... yesterday, we did very well ... but the score was Eldritch 4 deaths, Bard 2 deathes, Druid 2 deaths, and the tanks 1 death each. And I played the Lute and Song of Healing to aid the Healer in the group. It wasn't enough. We didn't lose experience or anything ... but it makes the inter mechanics difficult. I can't buff enough -- get bit on the amount of Constitution I have, and the Healing is better than my ability to tank. 
<br />

<br />
At level 40 to 50, the equivalent means ... YOU ARE NOT NEEDED! End of story! This is just projecting from what is happening now. I can already see the future for Eldritch's ... why bother? And unffortunately I do not see Mythic doing anything about this whatsoever. It's already apparent.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
